hashCode.name: hashCode
hashCode.comment:
Get a hash code for this object.

All objects have hash codes. Hash codes are guaranteed to be the same for objects that are equal when compared using the equality operator ==. Other than that there are no guarantees about the hash codes. They will not be consistent between runs and there are no distribution guarantees.

If a subclass overrides box2d/box2d.Transform.hashCode it should override the equality operator as well to maintain consistency.

constructors.comment: Constructs a new transform with a vector at the origin and no rotation.

copy.name: copy
copy.comment: Constructs a new transform equal to the given transform.

==.comment:
The equality operator.

The default behavior for all dart-core.Objects is to return true if and only if this and box2d/box2d.Transform.==.other are the same object.

Override this method to specify a different equality relation on a class. The overriding method must still be an equivalence relation. That is, it must be:

  • Total: It must return a boolean for all arguments. It should never throw or return null.

  • Reflexive: For all objects o, o == o must be true.

  • Symmetric: For all objects o1 and o2, o1 == o2 and o2 == o1 must either both be true, or both be false.

  • Transitive: For all objects o1, o2, and o3, if o1 == o2 and o2 == o3 are true, then o1 == o3 must be true.

The method should also be consistent over time, so equality of two objects should not change over time, or at least only change if one of the objects was modified.

If a subclass overrides the equality operator it should override the box2d/box2d.Transform.hashCode method as well to maintain consistency.

setFromPositionAndRotation.name: setFromPositionAndRotation
setFromPositionAndRotation.comment: Sets this transform with the given position and rotation.

setFrom.name: setFrom
setFrom.comment: Sets this transform equal to the given transform.

mul.name: mul
mul.comment: Multiply the given transform and given vector and return a new Vector2 with the result.

mulToOut.name: mulToOut
mulToOut.comment: Multiplies the given transform and the given vector and places the result in the given out parameter.

toString.name: toString
toString.comment: Returns a string representation of this object.

noSuchMethod.name: noSuchMethod
noSuchMethod.comment:
box2d/box2d.Transform.noSuchMethod is invoked when users invoke a non-existent method on an object. The name of the method and the arguments of the invocation are passed to box2d/box2d.Transform.noSuchMethod in an dart-core.Invocation. If box2d/box2d.Transform.noSuchMethod returns a value, that value becomes the result of the original invocation.

The default behavior of box2d/box2d.Transform.noSuchMethod is to throw a dart-core.NoSuchMethodError.
